### **(1) Translation into English**

**The Story of King Wu Hou and Wu Qi**

King Wu Hou of Wei was skilled in planning and decision-making, surpassing all his ministers. After a court session, he would often show signs of joy. Wu Qi, a general, approached and said, *"Have you ever heard the words of King Zhuang of Chu spoken to his attendants?"*

King Wu Hou asked, *"What did King Zhuang of Chu say?"*

Wu Qi replied:
*"King Zhuang of Chu was also skilled in planning and decision-making, surpassing all his ministers. Yet after court sessions, he would often appear worried. His advisor, Shen Gong Wu Chen, asked, ‘Why do Your Majesty appear worried after court sessions?’ King Zhuang replied, ‘I am worried because I am skilled in planning and decision-making, yet my ministers cannot match me. The ancient saying goes: ‘A ruler who relies only on himself will be overthrown; one who gains allies will become a hegemon; one who earns trust will survive; but one who relies solely on himself and no one equals him will perish.’ Now, with my unworthiness, if my ministers cannot match me, my state may soon perish! That is why I am worried.’"*

King Zhuang of Chu worried, but Your Majesty, you rejoice. King Wu Hou bowed twice in humility and said, *"Heaven has sent you, Master, to correct my mistakes."*

